# PulseWeaver

Self-hosted forward-auth sidecar. Single Go binary with embedded React SPA. Not yet released — code quality over backwards compatibility.

## Stack
- **Backend:** Go (Chi, SQLite, sqlx) — layered: Handler → Service → Repository → Database
- **Frontend:** React 19, TypeScript, Vite, shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS v4
- **API:** Schema-first OpenAPI — `api/openapi.yaml` is the single source of truth

## Key Paths
| Purpose | Path |
|---|---|
| Backend entry | `cmd/api/main.go` |
| Frontend entry | `frontend/src/main.tsx` |
| API spec | `api/openapi.yaml` |
| Migrations | `internal/database/migrations/` |
| Generated backend types | `internal/api/server.gen.go` (**do not modify**) |
| Generated frontend types | `frontend/src/lib/api/` (**do not modify**) |

## Commands
- `make dev-back` / `make dev-front` — hot-reload servers
- `make test` — all Go tests (always use this, not bare `go test ./...`; uses `-tags=test`)
- `make lint` / `make fix` — lint / lint + autofix
- `make api` — regenerate backend + frontend types from OpenAPI spec
- `make build` — full production build

